The paper discusses a cluster management system that employs a data-centric approach, which suggests that it may fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a 3-tier web-application architecture for system functions indicates that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions job scheduling and monitoring, which could fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the use of standard software suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
